  • Packages that use ThrottleConstraint 
    Package Description
    com.mashery.trafficmanager.model.core
    Provides classes and interfaces that comprise a view of the Mashery domain model from the Traffic Manager's point of view as it handles an API request.
    com.mashery.trafficmanager.model.oauth
    The package encapsulates the oauth authentication classes

    • Uses of ThrottleConstraint in com.mashery.trafficmanager.model.core

      Methods in com.mashery.trafficmanager.model.core that return ThrottleConstraint 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ThrottleConstraint Plan.getEffectiveThrottleConstraint()
      Returns the effective throttle constraint for this Plan or null if this Plan is not throttled.
      ThrottleConstraint APIKey.getEffectiveThrottleConstraint()
      Returns the effective throttle constraint for this Key or null if this Key is not throttle constrained.
      ThrottleConstraint PlanMethod.getEffectiveThrottleConstraint()
      Returns the effective throttle constraint for this Method or null if this Method is not throttled.
      ThrottleConstraint Plan.getKeyThrottleConstraint()
      Returns Key-specific throttle constraint for this Plan or null if this Plan does not allow overriding of throttle constraints by Keys.
      ThrottleConstraint APIEndpoint.getKeyThrottleConstraint()
      Returns the default throttle constraint for Key or null if Keys are not throttled on this endpoint
      ThrottleConstraint PlanMethod.getKeyThrottleConstraint()
      Returns Key-specific throttle constraint for this Method or null if the current Plan does not allow overriding of throttle constraints by Keys.
      ThrottleConstraint Key.getThrottleConstraint()
      Returns this Key's throttle constraint, or null if none is configured on this Key, or if this Key belongs to a Developer Class and the Developer Class does not allow throttle constraint overriding, or the Endpoint itself does not allow throttle constraint overriding by Keys.
      ThrottleConstraint API.getThrottleConstraint()
      Returns throttle constraint applied to this Service as a whole.
      ThrottleConstraint Plan.getThrottleConstraint()
      Returns the throttle constraint configured on this Plan or null if none.
      ThrottleConstraint DeveloperClass.getThrottleConstraint()
      Returns this Developer Class' throttle constraint, or null if none is configured on this Developer Class, or if the Endpoint does not allow overriding of throttle constraints
      ThrottleConstraint CustomerSite.getThrottleConstraint()
      Returns the optional Site-wide throttle constraint.
      ThrottleConstraint PlanMethod.getThrottleConstraint()
      Returns this Method's rate constraint or null if none.
